<plot>The artist Michael Flomen works with unexposed photographic paper and film. His darkroom is the outside world at night. To follow him in his creative practice, it was impossible to use any conventional light source. An infrared camera, utilizing the technique known as night vision, enabled us to capture him at work.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?629478</url></doc>
